  <entry>
    <id>tag:www.gov.uk,2005:PublicationesquePresenter/16305</id>
    <published>2012-06-18T01:00:00+01:00</published>
    <updated>2012-11-05T15:46:43+00:00</updated>
    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/total-greenhouse-gas-emissions-from-transport"/>
    <title>Total greenhouse gas emissions from transport</title>
    <category>Publication</category>
    <summary>Impact indicator, disaggregated by transport sector, published annually from May 2011.</summary>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;h2 id="dft-business-plan-input-indicator"&gt;DfT Business plan input indicator&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h3 id="geographical-coverage-united-kingdom"&gt;Geographical coverage: United Kingdom&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;h3 id="information-broken-down-by-domestic-transport-international-transport"&gt;Information broken down by: Domestic transport, international transport&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;h2 id="latest-data"&gt;Latest data&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In 2010, total greenhouse gas emissions for transport (inc. international) were 162.5 million tonnes of CO&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt; equivalent (MtCO&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt;e) with domestic transport greenhouse gas emissions being 121.9 MtCO&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt;e.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;Million tonnes of CO&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt; equivalent/Percentage&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a rel="external" href="http://charts.dft.gov.uk/dft-business-plan/indicators/#04"&gt;Click here to view this data in an interactive chart&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;table&gt;
&lt;thead&gt;&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;th&gt; &lt;/th&gt;
      &lt;th&gt;1990&lt;/th&gt;
      &lt;th&gt;2010&lt;/th&gt;
      &lt;th&gt;% change 1990 to 2010&lt;/th&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/thead&gt;
&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;Domestic transport&lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;td&gt;121.5&lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;td&gt;121.9&lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;td&gt;0.3&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;International transport&lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;td&gt;24.6&lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;td&gt;40.6&lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;td&gt;65.2&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;Total transport&lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;td&gt;146.1&lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;td&gt;162.5&lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;td&gt;11.2&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;&lt;h3 id="including-international-aviation-and-international-shipping"&gt;Including international aviation and international shipping&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;162.5 MtCO&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt;e in 2010&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Total greenhouse gas (&lt;abbr title="Domestic Greenhouse Gas"&gt;GHG&lt;/abbr&gt;) emissions from transport increased by 11% between 1990 (146.1 MtCO&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt;e) and 2010 (162.5 MtCO&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt;e)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h3 id="excluding-international-aviation-and-international-shipping"&gt;Excluding international aviation and international shipping&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;121.9 MtCO&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt;e in 2010&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Total domestic greenhouse gas (&lt;abbr title="Domestic Greenhouse Gas"&gt;GHG&lt;/abbr&gt;) emissions from transport were around the same level in 2010 (121.9 MtCO&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt;e) as in 1990 (121.5 MtCO&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt;e), making up 21% of total UK domestic greenhouse gas emissions in 2010.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h2 id="background-information"&gt;Background information&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The figures published for this indicator are the emissions from the basket of greenhouse gases covered by the Kyoto Protocol. In accordance with international reporting protocols, each of the gases is weighted by its global warming potential relative to that of carbon dioxide and presented in terms of the equivalent amount of carbon dioxide.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The data are compiled by &lt;abbr title="Department of Energy and Climate Change"&gt;DECC&lt;/abbr&gt; and its contractors on a calendar year basis due to the reporting timetable of the United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change (&lt;abbr title="United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change"&gt;UNFCCC&lt;/abbr&gt;) and the EU. The methodology behind the compilation from all sources, also agreed with the &lt;abbr title="United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change"&gt;UNFCCC&lt;/abbr&gt;, takes some time to work through and final results for the calendar year 2010 were published in February 2012. Results for 2011 will be published in early 2013.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;publishing schedule: annually&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;last updated: compiled from figures published by Department of Energy and Climate Change on 7 February 2012&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;next update: compiled by figures published the by Department of Energy and Climate Change on 5 February 2013&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h2 id="other-related-data-and-information"&gt;Other related data and information&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Further information on transport environment and energy statistics are available from the DfT website at:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-transport/series/energy-and-environment-statistics"&gt;Energy and environment statistics&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;Further greenhouse gas emission statistics are available from the &lt;abbr title="Department of Energy and Climate Change"&gt;DECC&lt;/abbr&gt; website at:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a rel="external" href="http://www.decc.gov.uk/en/content/cms/statistics/climate_stats/gg_emissions/gg_emissions.aspx"&gt;&lt;abbr title="Department of Energy and Climate Change"&gt;DECC&lt;/abbr&gt; greenhouse gas emissions statistics&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h2 id="further-information"&gt;Further information&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/department-for-transport-business-plan"&gt;Business Plan 2012-2015&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
